---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="DK App Tools"
  description="DK App Tools builds practical apps with clear purpose, local-first thinking, and simple user control."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Independent software brand</p>
        <h1>Practical apps with clear purpose.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          DK App Tools builds focused apps that do useful things clearly, without
          unnecessary accounts, noise, or dark-pattern nonsense.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button" href="/apps">View apps</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/support">Contact support</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-panel" aria-label="DK App Tools product preview">
        <div class="product-preview">
          <div class="preview-topbar">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span class="dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="preview-body">
            <p class="preview-kicker">First product</p>
            <div class="preview-title">Offline FileSecure</div>
            <div class="preview-list">
              <div class="preview-item">
                <span>Account</span>
                <strong>Not required</strong>
              </div>
              <div class="preview-item">
                <span>Storage</span>
                <strong>On device</strong>
              </div>
              <div class="preview-item">
                <span>Ads</span>
                <strong>None</strong>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Apps</p>
        <h2>Built around real use, not fake complexity.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        The first DK App Tools release is focused on local file protection. More
        apps may follow the same rule: useful, understandable, and direct.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card featured">
        <span class="card-label">Android app</span>
        <h3>Offline FileSecure</h3>
        <p>
          A simple offline vault for files you do not want exposed. Private files.
          Stored locally. Protected clearly.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="button" href="/apps/offline-filesecure">Learn about Offline FileSecure</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="card-label">Brand principle</span>
        <h3>No unnecessary noise</h3>
        <p>
          DK App Tools aims for apps that explain what they do and avoid bloated,
          confusing behavior.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Foundation</p>
        <h2>Small brand. Serious standards.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="card-label">Privacy-minded</span>
        <h3>Clear data behavior</h3>
        <p>
          Product pages and policies should explain what happens in plain language,
          not legal fog.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="card-label">Practical</span>
        <h3>Tools before hype</h3>
        <p>
          The goal is not to chase trends. The goal is to ship apps that solve
          concrete problems well.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="card-label">Independent</span>
        <h3>Built step by step</h3>
        <p>
          DK App Tools starts lean, with room to grow without pretending to be a
          giant corporation on day one.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
